---
import { withBase } from '../../utils/paths';
import DocsLayout from '../../components/docs/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Preventive Maintenance | PrintKeep by BMR Docs"
  description="Preventive maintenance guide for PrintKeep by BMR, covering planned reminders for routine printer care without replacing inspection."
  heading="Preventive maintenance is planned as a reminder workflow."
  intro="PrintKeep by BMR is intended to support routine maintenance planning, but it should not be presented as a safety system, automatic diagnostic tool, or replacement for manufacturer guidance."
>
  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="preventive-purpose-title">
    <h2 id="preventive-purpose-title">Purpose of preventive planning</h2>
    <p>
      Preventive maintenance planning is designed to help users remember routine checks before small issues become harder
      to understand. The planned workflow is conservative: create reminders, review the printer, record what happened,
      and adjust future notes based on real observations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="task-examples-title">
    <h2 id="task-examples-title">Possible routine tasks</h2>
    <ul class="plain-list">
      <li>Visual inspection before a long print job.</li>
      <li>Cleaning dust, filament debris, or residue from accessible areas.</li>
      <li>Checking belts, motion, fans, cable paths, or build surfaces according to manufacturer guidance.</li>
      <li>Reviewing previous notes before replacing a part or changing a maintenance interval.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="limits-title">
    <h2 id="limits-title">Important limits</h2>
    <p>
      Planned reminders should be treated as prompts only. They cannot confirm that a printer is safe, correctly tuned,
      or free of faults. Users remain responsible for inspection, safety, repair decisions, and following manufacturer
      printer documentation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-panel" aria-labelledby="preventive-next-title">
    <h2 id="preventive-next-title">Related documentation</h2>
    <ul class="link-list">
      <li><a href={withBase('/docs/maintenance-history/')}>Record completed maintenance</a></li>
      <li><a href={withBase('/docs/parts-and-consumables/')}>Document replacement parts</a></li>
      <li><a href={withBase('/features/')}>Review planned feature areas</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
